  <Name>k__BackingField: Hosea
  fancyName: 
  nickname: hos
  version: {fileID: 11400000, guid: bd3f8ba6a2445b646991a3e44f7f687a, type: 2}
  description: 
  chapters:
  - verses:
    - name: '1: '
      title: 
      number: 1
      content: '  The word of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> that came unto Hosea,
        the son of Beeri, in the days of Uzziah, Jotham, Ahaz, <i>and</i> Hezekiah,
        kings of Judah, and in the days of Jeroboam the son of Joash, king of Israel.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'The beginning of the word of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> by Hosea.
        And the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> said to Hosea, Go, take unto thee a wife
        of whoredoms and children of whoredoms: for the land hath committed great
        whoredom, <i>departing</i> from the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'So he went and took Gomer the daughter of Diblaim; which conceived,
        and bare him a son. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'And the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> said unto him, Call his name
        Jezreel; for yet a little <i>while</i>, and I will avenge the blood of Jezreel
        upon the house of Jehu, and will cause to cease the kingdom of the house
        of Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'And it shall come to pass at that day, that I will break the bow
        of Israel in the valley of Jezreel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'And she conceived again, and bare a daughter. And <i>God</i> said
        unto him, Call her name Lo-ruhamah: for I will no more have mercy upon the
        house of Israel; but I will utterly take them away. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'But I will have mercy upon the house of Judah, and will save them
        by the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> their God, and will not save them by bow,
        nor by sword, nor by battle, by horses, nor by horsemen. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Now when she had weaned Lo-ruhamah, she conceived, and bare a son. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Then said <i>God</i>, Call his name Lo-ammi: for ye <i>are</i> not
        my people, and I will not be your <i>God</i>.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Yet the number of the children of Israel shall be as the sand of
        the sea, which cannot be measured nor numbered; and it shall come to pass,
        <i>that</i> in the place where it was said unto them, Ye <i>are</i> not my
        people, <i>there</i> it shall be said unto them, <i>Ye are</i> the sons of
        the living God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Then shall the children of Judah and the children of Israel be gathered
        together, and appoint themselves one head, and they shall come up out of
        the land: for great <i>shall be</i> the day of Jezreel.'
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Israel, a Faithless Wife'
      title: Israel, a Faithless Wife
      number: 1
      content: '  Say ye unto your brethren, Ammi; and to your sisters, Ruhamah.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Plead with your mother, plead: for she <i>is</i> not my wife, neither
        <i>am</i> I her husband: let her therefore put away her whoredoms out of
        her sight, and her adulteries from between her breasts; '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'lest I strip her naked, and set her as in the day that she was born,
        and make her as a wilderness, and set her like a dry land, and slay her with
        thirst. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'And I will not have mercy upon her children; for they <i>be</i> the
        children of whoredoms. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'For their mother hath played the harlot: she that conceived them
        hath done shamefully: for she said, I will go after my lovers, that give
        <i>me</i> my bread and my water, my wool and my flax, mine oil and my drink. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Therefore, behold, I will hedge up thy way with thorns, and make
        a wall, that she shall not find her paths. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'And she shall follow after her lovers, but she shall not overtake
        them; and she shall seek them, but shall not find <i>them:</i> then shall
        she say, I will go and return to my first husband; for then <i>was it</i>
        better with me than now.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'For she did not know that I gave her corn, and wine, and oil, and
        multiplied her silver and gold, <i>which</i> they prepared for Baal. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Therefore will I return, and take away my corn in the time thereof,
        and my wine in the season thereof, and will recover my wool and my flax <i>given</i>
        to cover her nakedness. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'And now will I discover her lewdness in the sight of her lovers,
        and none shall deliver her out of mine hand. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'I will also cause all her mirth to cease, her feast days, her new
        moons, and her sabbaths, and all her solemn feasts. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'And I will destroy her vines and her fig trees, whereof she hath
        said, These <i>are</i> my rewards that my lovers have given me: and I will
        make them a forest, and the beasts of the field shall eat them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'And I will visit upon her the days of Baalim, wherein she burned
        incense to them, and she decked herself with her earrings and her jewels,
        and she went after her lovers, and forgat me, saith the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Therefore, behold, I will allure her, and bring her into the wilderness,
        and speak comfortably unto her. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'And I will give her her vineyards from thence, and the valley of
        Achor for a door of hope: and she shall sing there, as in the days of her
        youth, and as in the day when she came up out of the land of Egypt. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'And it shall be at that day, saith the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>,
        <i>that</i> thou shalt call me Ishi; and shalt call me no more Baali. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'For I will take away the names of Baalim out of her mouth, and they
        shall no more be remembered by their name. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'And in that day will I make a covenant for them with the beasts of
        the field, and with the fowls of heaven, and <i>with</i> the creeping things
        of the ground: and I will break the bow and the sword and the battle out
        of the earth, and will make them to lie down safely.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'And I will betroth thee unto me for ever; yea, I will betroth thee
        unto me in righteousness, and in judgment, and in lovingkindness, and in
        mercies. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'I will even betroth thee unto me in faithfulness: and thou shalt
        know the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'And it shall come to pass in that day, I will hear, saith the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>,
        I will hear the heavens, and they shall hear the earth; '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'and the earth shall hear the corn, and the wine, and the oil; and
        they shall hear Jezreel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: And I will sow her unto me in the earth; and I will have mercy upon
        her that had not obtained mercy; and I will say to <i>them which were</i>
        not my people, Thou <i>art</i> my people; and they shall say, <i>Thou art</i>
        my God.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Her Purchase Price'
      title: Her Purchase Price
      number: 1
      content: '  Then said the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> unto me, Go yet, love
        a woman beloved of <i>her</i> friend, yet an adulteress, according to the
        love of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> toward the children of Israel, who
        look to other gods, and love flagons of wine. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'So I bought her to me for fifteen <i>pieces</i> of silver, and <i>for</i>
        an homer of barley, and an half homer of barley: '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: Israel''s Return'
      title: Israel's Return
      number: 3
      content: 'and I said unto her, Thou shalt abide for me many days; thou shalt
        not play the harlot, and thou shalt not be for <i>another</i> man: so <i>will</i>
        I also <i>be</i> for thee.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'For the children of Israel shall abide many days without a king,
        and without a prince, and without a sacrifice, and without an image, and
        without an ephod, and <i>without</i> teraphim: '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: afterward shall the children of Israel return, and seek the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>
        their God, and David their king; and shall fear the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>
        and his goodness in the latter days.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The ''s Controversy'
      title: The 's Controversy
      number: 1
      content: '<smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>  Hear the word of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>,
        ye children of Israel: for the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> hath a controversy
        with the inhabitants of the land, because <i>there is</i> no truth, nor mercy,
        nor knowledge of God in the land. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'By swearing, and lying, and killing, and stealing, and committing
        adultery, they break out, and blood toucheth blood. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Therefore shall the land mourn, and every one that dwelleth therein
        shall languish, with the beasts of the field, and with the fowls of heaven;
        yea, the fishes of the sea also shall be taken away. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Yet let no man strive, nor reprove another: for thy people <i>are</i>
        as they that strive with the priest. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Therefore shalt thou fall in the day, and the prophet also shall
        fall with thee in the night, and I will destroy thy mother.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'My people are destroyed for lack of knowledge: because thou hast
        rejected knowledge, I will also reject thee, that thou shalt be no priest
        to me: seeing thou hast forgotten the law of thy God, I will also forget
        thy children. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'As they were increased, so they sinned against me: <i>therefore</i>
        will I change their glory into shame. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'They eat up the sin of my people, and they set their heart on their
        iniquity. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'And there shall be, like people, like priest: and I will punish them
        for their ways, and reward them their doings. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'For they shall eat, and not have enough: they shall commit whoredom,
        and shall not increase: because they have left off to take heed to the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Whoredom and wine and new wine take away the heart. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'My people ask counsel at their stocks, and their staff declareth
        unto them: for the spirit of whoredoms hath caused <i>them</i> to err, and
        they have gone a whoring from under their God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'They sacrifice upon the tops of the mountains, and burn incense upon
        the hills, under oaks and poplars and elms, because the shadow thereof <i>is</i>
        good: therefore your daughters shall commit whoredom, and your spouses shall
        commit adultery. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'I will not punish your daughters when they commit whoredom, nor your
        spouses when they commit adultery: for themselves are separated with whores,
        and they sacrifice with harlots: therefore the people <i>that</i> doth not
        understand shall fall.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Though thou, Israel, play the harlot, <i>yet</i> let not Judah offend;
        and come not ye unto Gilgal, neither go ye up to Beth-aven, nor swear, The
        <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> liveth. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'For Israel slideth back as a backsliding heifer: now the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>
        will feed them as a lamb in a large place. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Ephraim <i>is</i> joined to idols: let him alone. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Their drink is sour: they have committed whoredom continually: her
        rulers <i>with</i> shame do love, Give ye. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: The wind hath bound her up in her wings, and they shall be ashamed
        because of their sacrifices.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Against Priests and Kings'
      title: Against Priests and Kings
      number: 1
      content: '  Hear ye this, O priests; and hearken, ye house of Israel; and give
        ye ear, O house of the king; for judgment <i>is</i> toward you, because ye
        have been a snare on Mizpah, and a net spread upon Tabor. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'And the revolters are profound to make slaughter, though I <i>have
        been</i> a rebuker of them all.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'I know Ephraim, and Israel is not hid from me: for now, O Ephraim,
        thou committest whoredom, <i>and</i> Israel is defiled. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'They will not frame their doings to turn unto their God: for the
        spirit of whoredoms <i>is</i> in the midst of them, and they have not known
        the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'And the pride of Israel doth testify to his face: therefore shall
        Israel and Ephraim fall in their iniquity; Judah also shall fall with them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'They shall go with their flocks and with their herds to seek the
        <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>; but they shall not find <i>him</i>; he hath
        withdrawn himself from them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'They have dealt treacherously against the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>:
        for they have begotten strange children: now shall a month devour them with
        their portions.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Blow ye the cornet in Gibeah, <i>and</i> the trumpet in Ramah: cry
        aloud <i>at</i> Beth-aven, after thee, O Benjamin. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Ephraim shall be desolate in the day of rebuke: among the tribes
        of Israel have I made known that which shall surely be.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'The princes of Judah were like them that remove the bound: <i>therefore</i>
        I will pour out my wrath upon them like water. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Ephraim <i>is</i> oppressed <i>and</i> broken in judgment, because
        he willingly walked after the commandment. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Therefore <i>will</i> I <i>be</i> unto Ephraim as a moth, and to
        the house of Judah as rottenness. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'When Ephraim saw his sickness, and Judah <i>saw</i> his wound, then
        went Ephraim to the Assyrian, and sent to king Jareb: yet could he not heal
        you, nor cure you of your wound. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'For I <i>will be</i> unto Ephraim as a lion, and as a young lion
        to the house of Judah: I, <i>even</i> I, will tear and go away; I will take
        away, and none shall rescue <i>him</i>. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'I will go <i>and</i> return to my place, till they acknowledge their
        offence, and seek my face: in their affliction they will seek me early.'
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: A Brief Repentance'
      title: A Brief Repentance
      number: 1
      content: '  Come, and let us return unto the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>: for
        he hath torn, and he will heal us; he hath smitten, and he will bind us up. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'After two days will he revive us: in the third day he will raise
        us up, and we shall live in his sight. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Then shall we know, <i>if</i> we follow on to know the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>:
        his going forth is prepared as the morning; and he shall come unto us as
        the rain, as the latter <i>and</i> former rain unto the earth.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'O Ephraim, what shall I do unto thee? O Judah, what shall I do unto
        thee? for your goodness <i>is</i> as a morning cloud, and as the early dew
        it goeth away. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Therefore have I hewed <i>them</i> by the prophets; I have slain
        them by the words of my mouth: and thy judgments <i>are as</i> the light
        <i>that</i> goeth forth. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'For I desired mercy, and not sacrifice; and the knowledge of God
        more than burnt offerings.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'But they like men have transgressed the covenant: there have they
        dealt treacherously against me. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Gilead <i>is</i> a city of them that work iniquity, <i>and is</i>
        polluted with blood. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'And as troops of robbers wait for a man, <i>so</i> the company of
        priests murder in the way by consent: for they commit lewdness. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'I have seen an horrible thing in the house of Israel: there <i>is</i>
        the whoredom of Ephraim, Israel is defiled.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: Also, O Judah, he hath set an harvest for thee, when I returned the
        captivity of my people.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: A Half-baked Cake'
      title: A Half-baked Cake
      number: 1
      content: '  When I would have healed Israel, then the iniquity of Ephraim was
        discovered, and the wickedness of Samaria: for they commit falsehood; and
        the thief cometh in, <i>and</i> the troop of robbers spoileth without. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'And they consider not in their hearts <i>that</i> I remember all
        their wickedness: now their own doings have beset them about; they are before
        my face. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'They make the king glad with their wickedness, and the princes with
        their lies. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'They <i>are</i> all adulterers, as an oven heated by the baker, <i>who</i>
        ceaseth from raising after he hath kneaded the dough, until it be leavened. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'In the day of our king the princes have made <i>him</i> sick with
        bottles of wine; he stretched out his hand with scorners. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'For they have made ready their heart like an oven, whiles they lie
        in wait: their baker sleepeth all the night; in the morning it burneth as
        a flaming fire. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'They are all hot as an oven, and have devoured their judges; all
        their kings are fallen: <i>there is</i> none among them that calleth unto
        me.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Ephraim, he hath mixed himself among the people; Ephraim is a cake
        not turned. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Strangers have devoured his strength, and he knoweth <i>it</i> not:
        yea, gray hairs are here and there upon him, yet he knoweth not. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'And the pride of Israel testifieth to his face: and they do not return
        to the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> their God, nor seek him for all this. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Ephraim also is like a silly dove without heart: they call to Egypt,
        they go to Assyria. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'When they shall go, I will spread my net upon them; I will bring
        them down as the fowls of the heaven; I will chastise them, as their congregation
        hath heard. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Woe unto them! for they have fled from me: destruction unto them!
        because they have transgressed against me: though I have redeemed them, yet
        they have spoken lies against me. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'And they have not cried unto me with their heart, when they howled
        upon their beds: they assemble themselves for corn and wine, <i>and</i> they
        rebel against me. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Though I have bound <i>and</i> strengthened their arms, yet do they
        imagine mischief against me. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'They return, <i>but</i> not to the most High: they are like a deceitful
        bow: their princes shall fall by the sword for the rage of their tongue:
        this <i>shall be</i> their derision in the land of Egypt.'
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Reaping the Whirlwind'
      title: Reaping the Whirlwind
      number: 1
      content: '    <i>Set</i> the trumpet to thy mouth. <i>He shall come</i> as
        an eagle against the house of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>, because they
        have transgressed my covenant, and trespassed against my law. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Israel shall cry unto me, My God, we know thee.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Israel hath cast off <i>the thing that is</i> good: the enemy shall
        pursue him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'They have set up kings, but not by me: they have made princes, and
        I knew <i>it</i> not: of their silver and their gold have they made them
        idols, that they may be cut off.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Thy calf, O Samaria, hath cast <i>thee</i> off; mine anger is kindled
        against them: how long <i>will it be</i> ere they attain to innocency? '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'For from Israel <i>was</i> it also: the workman made it; therefore
        it <i>is</i> not God: but the calf of Samaria shall be broken in pieces.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'For they have sown the wind, and they shall reap the whirlwind: it
        hath no stalk: the bud shall yield no meal: if so be it yield, the strangers
        shall swallow it up. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Israel is swallowed up: now shall they be among the Gentiles as a
        vessel wherein <i>is</i> no pleasure. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'For they are gone up to Assyria, a wild ass alone by himself: Ephraim
        hath hired lovers. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Yea, though they have hired among the nations, now will I gather
        them, and they shall sorrow a little for the burden of the king of princes.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Because Ephraim hath made many altars to sin, altars shall be unto
        him to sin. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'I have written to him the great things of my law, <i>but</i> they
        were counted as a strange thing. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'They sacrifice flesh <i>for</i> the sacrifices of mine offerings,
        and eat <i>it; but</i> the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> accepteth them not;
        now will he remember their iniquity, and visit their sins: they shall return
        to Egypt. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'For Israel hath forgotten his Maker, and buildeth temples; and Judah
        hath multiplied fenced cities: but I will send a fire upon his cities, and
        it shall devour the palaces thereof.'
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Days of Recompence'
      title: Days of Recompence
      number: 1
      content: '  Rejoice not, O Israel, for joy, as <i>other</i> people: for thou
        hast gone a whoring from thy God, thou hast loved a reward upon every cornfloor. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'The floor and the winepress shall not feed them, and the new wine
        shall fail in her. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'They shall not dwell in the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>''s land;
        but Ephraim shall return to Egypt, and they shall eat unclean <i>things</i>
        in Assyria. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'They shall not offer wine <i>offerings</i> to the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>,
        neither shall they be pleasing unto him: their sacrifices <i>shall be</i>
        unto them as the bread of mourners; all that eat thereof shall be polluted:
        for their bread for their soul shall not come into the house of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'What will ye do in the solemn day, and in the day of the feast of
        the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>? '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'For, lo, they are gone because of destruction: Egypt shall gather
        them up, Memphis shall bury them: the pleasant <i>places</i> for their silver,
        nettles shall possess them: thorns <i>shall be</i> in their tabernacles. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'The days of visitation are come, the days of recompence are come;
        Israel shall know <i>it:</i> the prophet <i>is</i> a fool, the spiritual
        man <i>is</i> mad, for the multitude of thine iniquity, and the great hatred. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'The watchman of Ephraim <i>was</i> with my God: <i>but</i> the prophet
        <i>is</i> a snare of a fowler in all his ways, <i>and</i> hatred in the house
        of his God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'They have deeply corrupted <i>themselves</i>, as in the days of Gibeah:
        <i>therefore</i> he will remember their iniquity, he will visit their sins.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'I found Israel like grapes in the wilderness; I saw your fathers
        as the firstripe in the fig tree at her first time: <i>but</i> they went
        to Baal-peor, and separated themselves unto <i>that</i> shame; and <i>their</i>
        abominations were according as they loved. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: '<i>As for</i> Ephraim, their glory shall fly away like a bird, from
        the birth, and from the womb, and from the conception. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Though they bring up their children, yet will I bereave them, <i>that
        there shall</i> not <i>be</i> a man <i>left:</i> yea, woe also to them when
        I depart from them! '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Ephraim, as I saw Tyrus, <i>is</i> planted in a pleasant place: but
        Ephraim shall bring forth his children to the murderer. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Give them, O <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>: what wilt thou give? give
        them a miscarrying womb and dry breasts.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'All their wickedness <i>is</i> in Gilgal: for there I hated them:
        for the wickedness of their doings I will drive them out of mine house, I
        will love them no more: all their princes <i>are</i> revolters. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Ephraim is smitten, their root is dried up, they shall bear no fruit:
        yea, though they bring forth, yet will I slay <i>even</i> the beloved <i>fruit</i>
        of their womb. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'My God will cast them away, because they did not hearken unto him:
        and they shall be wanderers among the nations.'
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Their Divided Heart'
      title: Their Divided Heart
      number: 1
      content: '  Israel <i>is</i> an empty vine, he bringeth forth fruit unto himself:
        according to the multitude of his fruit he hath increased the altars; according
        to the goodness of his land they have made goodly images. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Their heart is divided; now shall they be found faulty: he shall
        break down their altars, he shall spoil their images. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'For now they shall say, We have no king, because we feared not the
        <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>; what then should a king do to us?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'They have spoken words, swearing falsely in making a covenant: thus
        judgment springeth up as hemlock in the furrows of the field. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'The inhabitants of Samaria shall fear because of the calves of Beth-aven:
        for the people thereof shall mourn over it, and the priests thereof <i>that</i>
        rejoiced on it, for the glory thereof, because it is departed from it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'It shall be also carried unto Assyria <i>for</i> a present to king
        Jareb: Ephraim shall receive shame, and Israel shall be ashamed of his own
        counsel.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: '  <i>As for</i> Samaria, her king is cut off as the foam upon the
        water. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'The high places also of Aven, the sin of Israel, shall be destroyed:
        the thorn and the thistle shall come up on their altars; and they shall say
        to the mountains, Cover us; and to the hills, Fall on us.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'O Israel, thou hast sinned from the days of Gibeah: there they stood:
        the battle in Gibeah against the children of iniquity did not overtake them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: '<i>It is</i> in my desire that I should chastise them; and the people
        shall be gathered against them, when they shall bind themselves in their
        two furrows. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'And Ephraim <i>is as</i> an heifer <i>that is</i> taught, <i>and</i>
        loveth to tread out <i>the corn</i>; but I passed over upon her fair neck:
        I will make Ephraim to ride; Judah shall plow, <i>and</i> Jacob shall break
        his clods.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Sow to yourselves in righteousness, reap in mercy; break up your
        fallow ground: for <i>it is</i> time to seek the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>,
        till he come and rain righteousness upon you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Ye have plowed wickedness, ye have reaped iniquity; ye have eaten
        the fruit of lies: because thou didst trust in thy way, in the multitude
        of thy mighty men.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Therefore shall a tumult arise among thy people, and all thy fortresses
        shall be spoiled, as Shalman spoiled Beth-arbel in the day of battle: the
        mother was dashed in pieces upon <i>her</i> children. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'So shall Beth-el do unto you because of your great wickedness: in
        a morning shall the king of Israel utterly be cut off.'
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Father''s Love'
      title: The Father's Love
      number: 1
      content: '  When Israel <i>was</i> a child, then I loved him, and called my
        son out of Egypt. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: '<i>As</i> they called them, so they went from them: they sacrificed
        unto Baalim, and burned incense to graven images.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'I taught Ephraim also to go, taking them by their arms; but they
        knew not that I healed them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'I drew them with cords of a man, with bands of love: and I was to
        them as they that take off the yoke on their jaws, and I laid meat unto them.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'He shall not return into the land of Egypt, but the Assyrian shall
        be his king, because they refused to return. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'And the sword shall abide on his cities, and shall consume his branches,
        and devour <i>them</i>, because of their own counsels. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'And my people are bent to backsliding from me: though they called
        them to the most High, none at all would exalt <i>him</i>.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'How shall I give thee up, Ephraim? <i>how</i> shall I deliver thee,
        Israel? how shall I make thee as Admah? <i>how</i> shall I set thee as Zeboim?
        mine heart is turned within me, my repentings are kindled together. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'I will not execute the fierceness of mine anger, I will not return
        to destroy Ephraim: for I <i>am</i> God, and not man; the Holy One in the
        midst of thee: and I will not enter into the city. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'They shall walk after the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>: he shall roar
        like a lion: when he shall roar, then the children shall tremble from the
        west. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'They shall tremble as a bird out of Egypt, and as a dove out of the
        land of Assyria: and I will place them in their houses, saith the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Ephraim compasseth me about with lies, and the house of Israel with
        deceit: but Judah yet ruleth with God, and is faithful with the saints.'
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: His Past Mercies'
      title: His Past Mercies
      number: 1
      content: '  Ephraim feedeth on wind, and followeth after the east wind: he
        daily increaseth lies and desolation; and they do make a covenant with the
        Assyrians, and oil is carried into Egypt.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'The <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> hath also a controversy with Judah,
        and will punish Jacob according to his ways; according to his doings will
        he recompense him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'He took his brother by the heel in the womb, and by his strength
        he had power with God: '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'yea, he had power over the angel, and prevailed: he wept, and made
        supplication unto him: he found him <i>in</i> Beth-el, and there he spake
        with us; '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'even the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> God of hosts; the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> 
        <i>is</i> his memorial. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Therefore turn thou to thy God: keep mercy and judgment, and wait
        on thy God continually.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: '  <i>He is</i> a merchant, the balances of deceit <i>are</i> in his
        hand: he loveth to oppress. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'And Ephraim said, Yet I am become rich, I have found me out substance:
        <i>in</i> all my labours they shall find none iniquity in me that <i>were</i>
        sin. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'And I <i>that am</i> the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> thy God from
        the land of Egypt will yet make thee to dwell in tabernacles, as in the days
        of the solemn feast.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'I have also spoken by the prophets, and I have multiplied visions,
        and used similitudes, by the ministry of the prophets. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: '<i>Is there</i> iniquity <i>in</i> Gilead? surely they are vanity:
        they sacrifice bullocks in Gilgal; yea, their altars <i>are</i> as heaps
        in the furrows of the fields. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'And Jacob fled into the country of Syria, and Israel served for a
        wife, and for a wife he kept <i>sheep</i>. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'And by a prophet the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> brought Israel out
        of Egypt, and by a prophet was he preserved. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Ephraim provoked <i>him</i> to anger most bitterly: therefore shall
        he leave his blood upon him, and his reproach shall his Lord return unto
        him.'
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Only Saviour'
      title: The Only Saviour
      number: 1
      content: '  When Ephraim spake trembling, he exalted himself in Israel; but
        when he offended in Baal, he died. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'And now they sin more and more, and have made them molten images
        of their silver, <i>and</i> idols according to their own understanding, all
        of it the work of the craftsmen: they say of them, Let the men that sacrifice
        kiss the calves. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Therefore they shall be as the morning cloud, and as the early dew
        that passeth away, as the chaff <i>that</i> is driven with the whirlwind
        out of the floor, and as the smoke out of the chimney.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Yet I <i>am</i> the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> thy God from the
        land of Egypt, and thou shalt know no god but me: for <i>there is</i> no
        saviour beside me. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'I did know thee in the wilderness, in the land of great drought. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'According to their pasture, so were they filled; they were filled,
        and their heart was exalted; therefore have they forgotten me. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Therefore I will be unto them as a lion: as a leopard by the way
        will I observe <i>them:</i>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'I will meet them as a bear <i>that is</i> bereaved <i>of her whelps</i>,
        and will rend the caul of their heart, and there will I devour them like
        a lion: the wild beast shall tear them.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'O Israel, thou hast destroyed thyself; but in me <i>is</i> thine
        help. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'I will be thy king: where <i>is any other</i> that may save thee
        in all thy cities? and thy judges of whom thou saidst, Give me a king and
        princes? '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'I gave thee a king in mine anger, and took <i>him</i> away in my
        wrath. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'The iniquity of Ephraim <i>is</i> bound up; his sin <i>is</i> hid. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'The sorrows of a travailing woman shall come upon him: he <i>is</i>
        an unwise son; for he should not stay long in <i>the place of</i> the breaking
        forth of children. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'I will ransom them from the power of the grave; I will redeem them
        from death: O death, I will be thy plagues; O grave, I will be thy destruction:
        repentance shall be hid from mine eyes.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Though he be fruitful among <i>his</i> brethren, an east wind shall
        come, the wind of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> shall come up from the
        wilderness, and his spring shall become dry, and his fountain shall be dried
        up: he shall spoil the treasure of all pleasant vessels. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Samaria shall become desolate; for she hath rebelled against her
        God: they shall fall by the sword: their infants shall be dashed in pieces,
        and their women with child shall be ripped up.'
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Return, O Israel!'
      title: Return, O Israel!
      number: 1
      content: '  O Israel, return unto the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> thy God;
        for thou hast fallen by thine iniquity. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Take with you words, and turn to the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>:
        say unto him, Take away all iniquity, and receive <i>us</i> graciously: so
        will we render the calves of our lips. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Asshur shall not save us; we will not ride upon horses: neither will
        we say any more to the work of our hands, <i>Ye are</i> our gods: for in
        thee the fatherless findeth mercy.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'I will heal their backsliding, I will love them freely: for mine
        anger is turned away from him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'I will be as the dew unto Israel: he shall grow as the lily, and
        cast forth his roots as Lebanon. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'His branches shall spread, and his beauty shall be as the olive tree,
        and his smell as Lebanon. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'They that dwell under his shadow shall return; they shall revive
        <i>as</i> the corn, and grow as the vine: the scent thereof <i>shall be</i>
        as the wine of Lebanon. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Ephraim <i>shall say</i>, What have I to do any more with idols?
        I have heard <i>him</i>, and observed him: I <i>am</i> like a green fir tree.
        From me is thy fruit found.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Who <i>is</i> wise, and he shall understand these <i>things?</i>
        prudent, and he shall know them? for the ways of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> 
        <i>are</i> right, and the just shall walk in them: but the transgressors
        shall fall therein.'
      comments: []
